{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2aac3861-f179-4f69-a130-bc2f60b27d62","content":"The issue is classic F# file ordering. In the `.fsproj`, `Services.fs` is listed **before** `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on types from `Domain.fs`. F# requires dependencies to appear first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01Kqg6hMaT3o4gPVjPzPLTdd","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-aca2090a340949dfb9bc1232a64f8669/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-aca2090a340949dfb9bc1232a64f8669/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"bbe82993-cea1-4ef9-ac51-cff740b44828","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed before them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. `Services.fs` — which `open`s `BrokenOrder.Domain`\n2. `Domain.fs` — defines `BrokenOrder.Domain`\n3. `Program.fs` — uses both\n\n`Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`. The fix is to put `Domain.fs` first.","outputTokens":371,"requestId":"C781:1C25F2:F25FDA:1319A5D:69FFD7B4"},"id":"7ca0c34b-7200-4fc6-8ccc-a6d0d1722c59","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:56:27.191Z","parentId":"fd46c09c-00d9-497d-83a3-a298b58413b0"}
